Title: Series: Four landscapes with the Holy Family on their Flight into Egypt
Description: The rest on the flight into Egypt. Landscape with Joseph leading the ass to a river at centre right and two angels seated next to the Virgin at left, who is about to wrap the nude Christ Child in a shawl; from a series of four plates; early, lightly bitten proof before letters. Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Herman van Swanevelt
Curator's comments: This is one from a series of four, for comment see 1844,0425.15. This is first state, for impressions of later states see 1844,0425.16 and S.2277. For a copy in reverse see F,2.233.
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts c.1450-1700 (8.I)
